        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(plugins): memoize loadInstalledPluginIndexInstallRecordsSync on hot path",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Memoize `loadInstalledPluginIndexInstallRecordsSync` result in `resolvePluginLoadCacheContext` so the sync file read does not fire on every `resolvePluginTools()` call, including LRU cache hits.\n- Invalidate the memoized install records alongside the plugin loader cache in `clearPluginLoaderCache`.\n\nInstall records do not change at runtime, so the synchronous file read was redundant after the first call. This was causing unnecessary I/O on every plugin tool resolution, compounding under concurrent embedded runs.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `resolvePluginLoadCacheContext` uses `getMemoizedInstallRecords` instead of direct `loadInstalledPluginIndexInstallRecordsSync`.\n- Cache cleared in `clearPluginLoaderCache`.\n- Existing tests in `installed-plugin-index-records.test.ts` and `installed-plugin-index.test.ts` exercise the underlying function and remain unaffected.\n\nCloses #77348",
        "branch": "fix/77348-memoize-install-records",
